    <!-- BODY + TOC -->
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_240px] gap-16 md:gap-20 py-20">
      <div class="max-w-2xl min-w-0">

        <p class="prose-body first-letter:float-left first-letter:text-[72px] first-letter:leading-[0.9] first-letter:mr-3 first-letter:mt-2 first-letter:text-[#13342D]">
          <strong>When Blueridge Retreats reached out in May 2025</strong>, they were running 22 cabins in the North Georgia mountains with a set-and-forget PriceLabs setup. Pacing was stuck: 64% average occupancy, a shoulder-season that felt like a black hole, and a pricing floor that hadn't moved in 18 months.
        </p>

        <p class="prose-body">The team — Sarah and her two cohosts — had the hardest problem in STR operations: everything looked fine from the dashboard. No single property was broken. They were getting bookings. The reviews were great. But the portfolio total wasn't growing, and the shoulder quarters were slowly eating into the peak.</p>

        <section id="sec-the-problem">
          <h2 class="prose-h2">The Problem</h2>
          <p class="prose-body">We pulled their 18-month booking history on the first call and ran it through our pacing analysis. Three things jumped out immediately:</p>
          <ol class="prose-ol">
            <li><strong>Weekend rates were compressed</strong> by 12–15% below the comp set's median. PriceLabs' min-price rule had been set too aggressively and was anchoring too low.</li>
            <li><strong>Midweek was dead</strong> — 31% occupancy across the portfolio in shoulder months, with a 3-night minimum stay fighting the math.</li>
            <li><strong>Length-of-stay discounts were non-existent</strong>, which meant 4-night bookings were paying the same rate-per-night as 2-night bookings. Portfolio-wide, this was leaving real money on the table.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section id="sec-what-we-did">
          <h2 class="prose-h2">What We Did</h2>
          <p class="prose-body">The RevFactor playbook for a portfolio this size runs in four phases, executed over the first 30 days:</p>

          <figure class="my-10">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506905925346-21bda4d32df4?auto=format&fit=crop&w=2000&q=85" alt="" class="w-full rounded-[16px]" />
            <figcaption class="text-[13px] text-[#8F6E62] text-center mt-3" style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',Georgia,serif; font-style:italic;">A typical Blueridge property. The pacing problem wasn't the listings — it was the rules around them.</figcaption>
          </figure>

          <ol class="prose-ol">
            <li><strong>Week 1: Audit & stabilize.</strong> We raised the min-price floor 12% across the portfolio and rebuilt each property's competitive set from scratch (most were still using PriceLabs' default 10-mile radius).</li>
            <li><strong>Week 2: Minimum stay restructure.</strong> Dropped from 3-night to 1-night minimum on Tuesday and Wednesday only. Weekend stayed at 2-night minimum. This alone lifted shoulder-season bookings 22%.</li>
            <li><strong>Week 3: Length-of-stay discounts.</strong> 10% off 4-night stays, 18% off 7+. Structured to incentivize exactly the guest profile Blueridge wanted — longer stays, fewer turnovers.</li>
            <li><strong>Week 4: Event calendar + forecast.</strong> Loaded 60 days of local events (concerts, festivals, weddings at nearby venues) into the forecast model with custom rate modifiers.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section id="sec-the-numbers">
          <h2 class="prose-h2">The Numbers</h2>
          <p class="prose-body">Month-over-month trajectory, 11 months after kickoff:</p>

          <div class="my-10 overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-[14px] border-collapse">
              <thead>
                <tr class="border-b-2 border-[#3F261F]">
                  {['Quarter', 'Revenue', 'Occupancy', 'ADR', 'RevPAR lift'].map(h => (
                    <th class="text-left py-3 px-3 font-bold uppercase text-[10px] tracking-[2px] text-[#3F261F]">{h}</th>
                  ))}
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">
                <tr class="border-b border-[#C8C4BC]"><td class="py-3 px-3" style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',Georgia,serif;">Pre-RevFactor baseline</td><td class="py-3 px-3 tabular-nums">—</td><td class="py-3 px-3 tabular-nums">64%</td><td class="py-3 px-3 tabular-nums">$261</td><td class="py-3 px-3 tabular-nums">—</td></tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-[#C8C4BC]"><td class="py-3 px-3" style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',Georgia,serif;">Q3 2025 (ramp)</td><td class="py-3 px-3 tabular-nums">+$38K</td><td class="py-3 px-3 tabular-nums">67%</td><td class="py-3 px-3 tabular-nums">$278</td><td class="py-3 px-3 tabular-nums text-[#5D6D59]">+8.9%</td></tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-[#C8C4BC]"><td class="py-3 px-3" style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',Georgia,serif;">Q4 2025 (peak)</td><td class="py-3 px-3 tabular-nums">+$62K</td><td class="py-3 px-3 tabular-nums">73%</td><td class="py-3 px-3 tabular-nums">$298</td><td class="py-3 px-3 tabular-nums text-[#5D6D59]">+14.2%</td></tr>
