        <section id="sec-playbook">
          <h2 class="prose-h2">The Playbook You Can Run</h2>
          <p class="prose-body">You don't need to be a RevFactor client to run this playbook. If you operate a small-to-mid portfolio and you're where Blueridge was in May 2025, these are the five moves that account for ~80% of the lift:</p>
          <ul class="prose-ul">
            <li>Audit your PriceLabs min-price floor. If it hasn't moved in 12 months, it's probably too low.</li>
            <li>Rebuild your comp set. Don't let PriceLabs default the radius — pick 8–12 properties you'd actually compete against.</li>
            <li>Separate your midweek and weekend minimum stays. They're different markets.</li>
            <li>Add length-of-stay discounts that start at 4 nights. Target the guest profile you want.</li>
            <li>Load the local event calendar at least 60 days out. Set custom rate modifiers for each.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="prose-body">What RevFactor adds on top: daily monitoring, competitive rate shifts, and the judgment calls the dashboard can't make for you. If you want to see what we'd do with your portfolio, <a href="/" class="text-[#13342D] underline underline-offset-4 decoration-[#C8C4BC] hover:decoration-[#13342D]">start here</a>.</p>
        </section>

